{
  "texts": [
    "Considering more comprehensive factors in evaluation.",
    "While accuracy is crucial in evaluating LLMs for math problem-solving, it shouldn't be the sole metric.",
    "Other important dimensions include: i) Confidence Provision: Imani et al. (2023)'s \"MathPromper\" boosts LLM performance and confidence by generating algebraic expressions, providing diverse prompts, and evaluating consensus among multiple runs.",
    "ii) Verifiable Explanations: Gaur and Saunshi (2023) used concise, verifiable explanations to assess LLM reasoning, revealing their proficiency in zero-shot solving of symbolic MWPand their ability to produce succinct explanations.",
    "Learning to select in-context examples."
  ]
}